{"id":83308,"title":"The use of diaries to promote recovery after critical illness.","abstract":"Admission to intensive care exposes patients and family members to extreme physical and psychological stress. This stress may cause anxiety, depression and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), which impairs their recovery. Nurses are actively seeking solutions and tools to assist patients and family members to recover after admission to intensive care.","date":"2014-12-02","categories":"Pathological Conditions and Signs and Symptoms","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25438470","annotations":[{"name":"Posttraumatic stress disorder","weight":0.872094,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posttraumatic_stress_disorder"},{"name":"Illness","weight":0.812486,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illness"},{"name":"Major depressive disorder","weight":0.759865,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Major_depressive_disorder"},{"name":"Anxiety","weight":0.718103,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anxiety"},{"name":"Stress (biology)","weight":0.709797,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stress_(biology)"},{"name":"Psychology","weight":0.708098,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.640172,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Intensive-care medicine","weight":0.614952,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive-care_medicine"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.603856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Family","weight":0.234085,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Family"},{"name":"Physics","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physics"},{"name":"Diary","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diary"}]}
